reviewText:
you want to laugh a lot and see some older actors and get a look back of of hee haw?
you should watch all of these people, it will bring back old memories with a laugh
see a couple of them way back when they started out in the business
all good comedians!
It was funny thanks a bunch
Helps keep mom entertained.  At 86 with dementia it is important that we keep mom amused.  This DVD works!

I just watched this with a friend of mine, and we agreed that George "Goober" Lindsey and
Foster Brooks were funny, but nobody else was. Weak humor by and large, we thought, but if
you're a fan of the other comedians, go for it. Surprisingly, Jeff Foxworthy wasn't funny, either -
he got better later, I guess.
I thought there would be more time with the comedians, but at least they were more family oriented than today's material.
NICE DVD I LIKED IT VERY MUCH. HOPE TO FIND MORE DVDS LIKE THIS AGAIN. THANKS AGAIN. WILLIAM
